content:
Too similar to Isoland 1 for me to be particularly excited about playing a 
third game. The characters' philosophical musings have (like the first 
game) no apparent connection to the alien symbology and there's no 
narrative payoff or any deeper understanding of the game world. Maybe just 
get rid of NPCs next time and communicate via etchings, notes and alien 
tech or such-like? Edit: I have completed the game twice without hints. I 
understand the NPCs provide clues and I follow them. However, the rest of 
what they say is, albeit inoffensively whimsical, no substitute for a 
compelling narrative. If you're not interested in constructive criticism, 
that's fine, there are plenty of other games out there.

Please pay attention to the hints and interaction in appeared in game.
